Kings (crown) often do not want to look in the mirror => mistakes, so the fool try to show the king his own stupidity without being killed (jester's licence)

In the Middle Ages a fool or a Tor (german: töricht = foolish) was the person, who entertained the royal household and was dressed mostly strange. The term "fool" also refers to persons who are very immature, stupid, clumsy, biased, prejudiced, ignorant, and who are based on their ignorance as scholars, theoretically.
